<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-29-0137 </DOCNO><TEXT>NATAS is a US Department of Energy (DOE) program that provides tailoredtechnical and commercialization assistance to users of energy-relatedappropriate technologies. NATAS helps individuals using conservationand renewable energy products and services and provides business assistanceto entrepreneurs and innovators in these fields. NATAS is operated forDOE by the National Center for Appropriate Technology (NCAT), which hasprovided information and technical assistance on appropriate technologiesfor 10 years. Since 1984, NATAS has responded to almost 25,000 inquiries.A database was created to catalog the types of users, their questionsand their assistance needs. Described is the evolution of those needsduring this period. An analysis of the public's changing needs for assistanceis presented in the context of concurrent developments (or lack thereof)of new technologies and methods. The analysis is intended to provideinsight about technology transfer and input to interest parties on whatappears to need transfer and why.</TEXT></DOC>